<br>
Aside from green mobs and getting mauled by 5 mids in Caledonia I only had 2 fights worth mentioning.  I was farming rocots in DF for emeralds so some scout could get a bow when a Koby SB hits me from behind with BS2 thus stunning me, since I don't have Purge I simply waited for the stun to wear off then IP'd and turned on him.  It was fabulous he could hardly hit me with all the parrying, then I hit Dirt since I hadn't tested it out yet and it worked great ... end result one very dead (and probably quite frustrated) SB.  Then a bit later I got invited into a small group with an Infy, Theurgy and Necro as there were 3 hibs coming up, a chanter a bard and a druid.  Well, since we had NO healing and the thergy managed to pick up mob aggro, thus placing him out of the fight we ended up getting slaughtered.  I did manage to be the last to die, however with 2 healing classes and alternately attacking the chanter to make sure he kept running and not casting, there wasn't much I could do in terms of actually killing any of them at that point :-/  It was still quite fun though, took them a good minute or so after I was alone for them to kill me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Nirala HammahMastah<br>
